Police in Bloemfontein on Wednesday said they were looking for a former policeman who is thought to be in the Durban to assist them with two rape cases. Parkroad Family, Child and Sexual Offences Unit are looking for Andries Albertus De Villiers, 47, known as Albert who can assist the police in two separate rape cases that happened in Bloemfontein, 2006, and KwaZulu-Natal, 2015, said Constable Maselela Langa in a statement. Albert was last seen in Brits, and now it believed that he is in Durban. Police said anyone who might know his whereabouts can contact Investigating Officer Detective WO Arlene Snyman on 082 527 7063 or 082 301 6390.